  "text": "The model developed in the Sirinhaém River was, to the greatest possible extent, based on local studies, the diet of the main consumers and fishery statistics (snook, Diapterus spp., pemecou sea catfish, other catfish and mullet). We also conducted specific sampling in the area to estimate the biomass of several groups (all fish, with exception of mullet, fiddler crab and polychaete groups). We applied the catchability coefficient of [CITATION_1] to balance the gear selection bias in the fish biomass assessment.",
